7/ As early-stage CEO
column4: be the top bug filer and top support person on the team. Team looks to you to model behavior.

text: 6/ Let every team member directly interact with real users. Talking to a disappointed customer makes solutions very clear.
5/ Force entire team to give public demos of product. Rough edges become evident when you find yourself trying to skip thru part of flow.
4/ Celebrate craftsmanship internally. Little details often get overshadowed by large achievements
column4: but users touch the details.

text: 3/ Have an example of someone else's perfect product to point to. There is no objective measure
column4: but relative subjectives are effective.

text: 2/ Have a clear mission that everyone on the team aligns around. Test this by having team members explain the mission themselves.
